room_title: Escape room "Mr. Dupree's Office" by Escape MSP in Minneapolis - St. Paul
review: We had a great type tracking down evidence against Dupree but I may be biased since we crushed it. We won with 9:30 left on the clock. Highly recommended.

room_title: Escape room "Mr. Dupree's Office" by Escape MSP in Minneapolis - St. Paul
review: This was a ton of fun! I've done four puzzle rooms now, and two of them have been through Escape MSP. Loved both! Really well designed rooms, fun tricks, cool atmosphere, delightful staff.

room_title: Escape room "Mr. Dupree's Office" by Escape MSP in Minneapolis - St. Paul
review: It was awesome! We had no idea what to expect and they totally delivered an amazing and unique experience. Well worth the money!

room_title: Escape room "Mr. Dupree's Office" by Escape MSP in Minneapolis - St. Paul
review: I went with a friend and we were paired up with a group of 8 others for Mr. Dupree's Office. We had a great time! One puzzle or clue led to the next and kept us all busy, thinking and working together. I can't wait to do James Bomb next! The staff member working Mr. Dupree's Office was great, too!

room_title: Escape room "Mr. Dupree's Office" by Escape MSP in Minneapolis - St. Paul
review: This place is super awesome! The guys working there were wonderful! It is definitely a challenge, but a doable challenge! Can't wait to go back and try the other room!

room_title: Escape room "Mr. Dupree's Office" by Escape MSP in Minneapolis - St. Paul
review: Great fun! I, too, was with a group of co-workers doing team building. All through the rest of the day we talked (and laughed) about the various clues, who did what, etc. Whether as a work activity, or as something different to do with family / friends, I highly recommend Escape MSP. I would love to do more scenarios.

room_title: Escape room "Mr. Dupree's Office" by Escape MSP in Minneapolis - St. Paul
review: I thought that I would be able to handle the puzzles not problem. I was wrong. It was definitely challenging and a lot of fun. They would also give us hints when were were really close but stuck on something small, which helped keep the game going. Teamwork and cleverness were key. I can't wait to come do the other room soon!
